<body class="ignore-math">
<h5 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h5>
<p>Suppose <span class="process-math">\(f^\prime(x)\neq{}f(x)\)</span> Show that if</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\left(f\cdot g\right)^\prime(x) = f^\prime(x)\cdot g^\prime(x)
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">then<aside class="aside aside-like"><h5 class="heading"><span class="title">Advice and Encouragement.</span></h5>
<p>Don't let this formula frighten you. Recall that <span class="process-math">\(\exp(x)=e^x\text{.}\)</span></p></aside></p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation}
g(x)=\exp\left({\int{\frac{1}{1-\frac{f(x)}{f^\prime(x)}}}\dx{x}{}}\right)\tag{1.4}
\end{equation}
</div>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-4.html#p-84" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
</body>
